    92	     * to clients. But care should be taken to avoid including any information in the exception message that
    93	     * should not be leaked to unauthenticated clients. It may be safer to throw {@link SaslException} in
    94	     * most cases so that a standard error message is returned to clients.
    95	     * </p>
